summary: These are my Chen Sisters. Body options: 7Base BBP, 7 Base TBBP HDT, ADEC, ADEC TBBP, CBBE, CBBE TBBP, UNPB and UNPB BBP.

[img]http://i.imgur.com/cUjlngk.png[/img]

[font=Georgia][color=#b4a7d6][size=4][b][i]Those are my Chen Sisters with 7Base TBBP HDT Body. Optional 7Base BBP, ADEC, ADEC TBBP, CBBE, CBBE TBBP, UNPB and UNPB BBP.[/i][/b][/size][/color][/font]

[font=Georgia][size=3][b][i][color=Slateblue]This is a Standalone Mod, don't need nothing else[/color][/i][/b][/size][/font]

[font=Georgia][color=#b4a7d6][size=3][b][i]Recommend:[/i][/b][/size][/color][/font]
[i][color=Slateblue][font=Georgia][size=3]For All BBP_TBBP Versions: These body options do have extra requirements refer to those mod pages if you need extra help
-NOTE: To run any BBP/TBBP-Body version Mod properly, you have to install a skeleton which supports BBP or TBBP such as XP32's XP32 Maximum Skeleton, which is what i have used. If not you'll get a crash at startup.
There are several skeleton/animation/package options out there to choose from.[/size][/font]
[/color][/i]


[font=Georgia][color=#b4a7d6][size=4][b][i]Manually Installation:[/i][/b][/size][/color][/font]
[font=Georgia][size=3][b][i][color=Blueviolet]Copy the ESP, Meshes and Textures-Folder[/color][/i]
[i][color=Blueviolet]and paste it in your Data- Folder,[/color][/i]
[i][color=Blueviolet]and confirm to overwrite if you already[/color][/i]
[i][color=Blueviolet]have a Meshes and Textures Folder there.[/color][/i][/b][/size][/font]
